# Changelog

## libtmux-mcp 0.1.x (unreleased)

<!-- KEEP THIS PLACEHOLDER - DO NOT REMOVE OR MODIFY THIS LINE -->
_Notes on upcoming releases will be added here_
<!-- END PLACEHOLDER - ADD NEW CHANGELOG ENTRIES BELOW THIS LINE -->

### Breaking changes

- `search_panes` now returns a structured `SearchPanesResult` wrapper
  instead of a bare `list[PaneContentMatch]`. The previous top-level
  list is available as `result.matches`; new fields surface pagination
  state (`truncated`, `truncated_panes`, `total_panes_matched`,
  `offset`, `limit`) so agents can detect when the result set was
  capped and re-request subsequent pages with a higher `offset`.
  Migration for clients iterating the old shape: replace
  `for m in search_panes(...)` with
  `for m in search_panes(...).matches`.
- `fastmcp>=3.2.4` minimum (was `>=3.1.0`). Required for
  `ReadonlyRetryMiddleware` to retry through the production tool
  decorator path; under earlier fastmcp versions the middleware was
  a no-op.

### What's new

- `show_buffer` now bounds its response with `max_lines` (default 500,
  matches `capture_pane`) and reports truncation via
  `BufferContent.content_truncated` and
  `BufferContent.content_truncated_lines`. A pathological
  `load_buffer` staging can no longer dump unbounded content into the
  model context on a single `show_buffer` call. Pass `max_lines=None`
  for a full-buffer read.
- New tools: `list_servers`, `snapshot_pane`, `wait_for_text`,
  `wait_for_content_change`, `wait_for_channel` / `signal_channel`,
  buffer lifecycle (`load_buffer`, `paste_buffer`, `show_buffer`,
  `delete_buffer`), hook introspection (`show_hook`, `show_hooks`),
  plus pane / session / window helpers (`pipe_pane`,
  `display_message`, copy-mode entry/exit, `paste_text`,
  `select_pane`, `swap_pane`, `select_window`, `move_window`).
- Middleware stack: `TimingMiddleware`, `ErrorHandlingMiddleware`,
  `AuditMiddleware` (digest-redacted argument summaries with
  sensitive-payload protection), `SafetyMiddleware` (tier-gated
  tool visibility), `ReadonlyRetryMiddleware` (transparent retry of
  readonly tools on transient `LibTmuxException` — mutating tools
  never retry), `TailPreservingResponseLimitingMiddleware` (caps
  oversized output while keeping the tail).
- Four recipe prompts: `run_and_wait`, `diagnose_failing_pane`,
  `build_dev_workspace`, `interrupt_gracefully`. Optional
  `PromptsAsTools` transform (env-gated via
  `LIBTMUX_MCP_PROMPTS_AS_TOOLS=1`) lets tools-only MCP clients
  reach them.
- `wait_for_text` / `wait_for_content_change` emit
  `ctx.report_progress` and `ctx.warning` notifications, and
  propagate `asyncio.CancelledError` cleanly so MCP clients can
  abort long waits.
- Best-effort lifespan-shutdown GC for leaked `libtmux_mcp_*` paste
  buffers — agents that miss `delete_buffer` no longer pollute the
  tmux server's buffer namespace across MCP restarts.
- Tool input schemas now carry per-parameter `description` fields
  auto-extracted from existing NumPy-style docstrings (free with
  the fastmcp 3.2.4 bump).

### Fixes

- `build_dev_workspace` prompt recipe now uses the real tool parameter
  names (`session_name=`, `pane_id=`, `direction=`) instead of
  non-existent aliases. A new prompt-alignment test prevents future
  drift between prompt text and tool signatures. The Linux-specific
  `/var/log/syslog` example is replaced with an OS-neutral
  `watch -n 1 date` default; callers can override via the new
  `log_command` parameter.
- `build_dev_workspace` no longer instructs agents to wait for shell
  prompts after launching screen-grabbing programs (`vim`, `watch`,
  `tail -f`). Eliminates a class of false-positive timeouts on
  agents following the recipe literally.
- macOS `TMUX_TMPDIR` self-kill guard: `_effective_socket_path`
  queries tmux directly via `display-message #{socket_path}` before
  falling back to env-based reconstruction; `_caller_is_on_server`
  adds a basename-match fallback to close the residual launchd-
  divergence gap.
- `search_panes` neutralizes tmux format-string injection in the
  regex fast path.
- `ReadonlyRetryMiddleware` retry warnings route through
  `libtmux_mcp.retry` (was fastmcp's stock `fastmcp.retry`) so they
  appear on the project's audit-stream namespace.

### Documentation

- New per-tool docs pages: `buffers.md`, `hooks.md`, `waits.md`,
  `tools/index.md`. Updated `panes.md` documents the
  `SearchPanesResult` shape and migration from the previous flat
  list. `docs/topics/safety.md` documents the macOS `TMUX_TMPDIR`
  self-kill caveat, the audit log, `pipe_pane`, and
  `set_environment`.

## libtmux-mcp 0.1.0a1 (2026-04-13)

### What's new

- New pane tools: `snapshot_pane`, `wait_for_content_change`, `select_pane`, `swap_pane`, `pipe_pane`, `display_message`, `enter_copy_mode`, `exit_copy_mode`, and `paste_text` (#11)
- New session tool: `select_window` — navigate by ID, index, or direction (#11)
- New window tool: `move_window` — reorder within a session or move across sessions (#11)
- New models: `PaneSnapshot` and `ContentChangeResult` (#11)

### Documentation

- Visual improvements to API docs from [gp-sphinx](https://gp-sphinx.git-pull.com)-based Sphinx packages (#10)
- Bump gp-sphinx docs stack to v0.0.1a8 (#14)

## libtmux-mcp 0.1.0a0 (2026-03-22)

### New features

- Initial release as standalone package
- MCP tools across 6 modules (server, session, window, pane, options, environment)
- `tmux://` URI resources for browsing tmux hierarchy
- Safety tier middleware (`readonly`, `mutating`, `destructive`)
- Socket isolation via `LIBTMUX_SOCKET` / `LIBTMUX_SOCKET_PATH` env vars
- Agent self-awareness via `TMUX_PANE` detection
- Server caching with `is_alive()` eviction
- Pydantic models for all tool outputs
- Full type safety (mypy strict)
